cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.MA. 

The paper studies logit choice dynamics in the context of local interaction games, which are a type of game theory model used to study complex social phenomena. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses properties of the dynamics in the context of social graphs, which suggests the category cs.SOC (Computer Science and Society) as a likely second choice. The paper also involves the study of observables and mixing time, which could fall under cs.SI (Computer Science and Information Theory) and cs.DS (Computer Science and Data Structures and Algorithms), respectively. Finally, the paper involves the study of randomized best response dynamics, which could fall under cs.MA (Computer Science and Multiagent Systems).
